    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>It would be possible to define ναός[a] temple, sanctuary ({D:7.15}) in such a way as to include both sanctuaries as well as replicas of such buildings, but in view of the widespread diminutive derivations in Greek and the clear distinctions which many languages make between originals and souvenir replicas, there seem to be both theoretical as well as practical reasons for this distinction between ναός[a] and ναός[b].</Content>
    </Note>
